Name: Google Docs
Title: Thinkspace Interest Form
Description:
Hi there! If you're interested in making a dent in entrepreneurship at Yale, we invite you to become a part of Thinkspace. We are a club encouraging entrepreneurship offline and online by connecting entrepreneurs, creatives and thinkers with each other and with the right resources. Our primary aim is building out a dead-simple web-platform, and our secondary aim is providing programming and workshops that revolve around this platform. 

Things are rolling along nicely, and we are excited at the prospect of building out partnerships with Tsai CITY, the CEID and Yale Launch, to name a few. And we could use your help and ideas!

Please take a couple of minutes to fill out this form. 

Questions? Contact: sarim.abbas@yale.edu felicia.chang@yale.edu
Message:
Hi everyone! The past year, Felicia Chang and I have been busy with a new club called Thinkspace. We are trying to encourage entrepreneurship on campus with a web-platform, and accompanying offline events. There are a lot of talented Yalies with great ideas, but unfortunately not all the resources are there. In particular, bringing together a team and securing funding can be difficult. So with our club, we are trying to build up a network of thinkers, programmers, engineers, artistsâ¦all kinds of creatives. So far weâve got a good response from Tsai, CEID and the like, and work is progressing steadily on the platform. 

Weâd love to get as many people interested and contributing. You can indicate your interest in the form below, and weâll keep you in the loop :) Thanks for reading!
